{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place flour, water, sugar, yeast, salt and oil into mixing bowl and knead <b>2 min\/<b>. Transfer dough to a clean work surface and cover with a kitchen towel.","Place 4 oz mozzarella cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place butter, garlic and Italian seasoning into mixing bowl and cook <b>4 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Divide dough into 1 oz balls (approx. 27 balls). Flatten with the palm of your hand and place 1 slice of pepperoni and 1 cube of remaining cheese in the center of each piece of dough. Fold edges up, pinch to close and gently reshape into balls.","Dip each stuffed dough ball into reserved melted butter mixture, coating all sides. Evenly layer buttered balls into a bundt pan while sprinkling reserved grated cheese and remaining 28-33 pepperoni slices between layers. Cover with cling wrap and let rise in a warm place for one hour or until doubled in size and dough springs back when touched. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 375°F.","Once dough has risen in pan, bake for 35 minutes (375°F) until golden brown. Let cool 5 minutes in pan before inverting onto a serving plate. Serve warm with marinara sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["16 oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","9 oz water, room temperature","½ oz sugar","1 packet\/envelope rapid rise yeast","2 tsp salt","1 oz olive oil","7 ½ oz low-moisture mozzarella, cubed (½ in.), divided","4 oz unsalted butter, cut into pieces","2 garlic cloves, crushed","2 tsp Italian seasoning","55 - 60 slices pepperoni (approx. 3.5 oz), divided","8 oz marinara sauce, to serve"]}],"id":"r280518","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-fohTP_ib3Aw\/XZan0TK5lwI\/AAAAAAAAhEM\/Ds0q3qs6jU448M579So2FgjeQWrtHKhmACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_VBRvyccTw9UiTRo4.png","title":"Pizza Monkey Bread","publishedAt":"2018-01-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"8 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"14 g","calories":"615 kJ \/ 147 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving plate, clean kitchen towel, bundt pan, cling wrap, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To reheat Pizza Monkey Bread: place on a baking sheet and cover loosely with foil. Bake for 15-20 minutes (350°F) or until warmed through.","Use your oven's proofing feature or heat oven to 100°F and place dough inside to proof."],"basicInfo":["advanced","45m","2h 30m","27 pieces"]}